WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.390 --> 00:00:08.330 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:10.290 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.290 --> 00:00:13.230 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:13.230 --> 00:00:22.560 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:25.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: I am a
lover of historical fiction.

00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:27.330 align:middle line:10%
It brings life's
dilemmas and the emotions

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:29.670 align:middle line:10%
that drive them into
the historical themes,

00:00:29.670 --> 00:00:30.920 align:middle line:10%
so they come alive.

00:00:30.920 --> 00:00:33.090 align:middle line:84%
In Barbara Hand Clow's
new work of fiction,

00:00:33.090 --> 00:00:35.400 align:middle line:84%
"Revelations of
the Aquarian Age,"

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:38.430 align:middle line:84%
a stark history of abuse
within the Catholic church,

00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:42.000 align:middle line:84%
extraordinarily wealthy ancient
bloodlines, and the process

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.260 align:middle line:84%
of healing together in a
bold story of revelations.

00:00:46.260 --> 00:00:49.770 align:middle line:84%
This is a thing that
some other authors have

00:00:49.770 --> 00:00:53.820 align:middle line:84%
tried to do as well, which is to
weave together these incredibly

00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:58.350 align:middle line:84%
complex themes without having
your character assassinated,

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:00.902 align:middle line:84%
which would happen if you
wrote it as non-fiction.

00:01:00.902 --> 00:01:03.360 align:middle line:84%
>>BARBARA HAND CLOW: Well,
there wouldn't be any characters

00:01:03.360 --> 00:01:03.840 align:middle line:90%
if it was non-fiction.

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:04.349 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know.

00:01:04.349 --> 00:01:05.724 align:middle line:84%
There wouldn't be
any characters.

00:01:05.724 --> 00:01:09.290 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, even weaving the
themes together is challenging.

00:01:09.290 --> 00:01:11.910 align:middle line:10%
And you can do this
any way you want.

00:01:11.910 --> 00:01:13.760 align:middle line:10%
And it's a lovely journey.

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:15.750 align:middle line:90%
It's a really interesting ride.

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:17.740 align:middle line:10%
So first of all, before
we go any further,

00:01:17.740 --> 00:01:20.910 align:middle line:10%
let's talk about the first
book where we ended up,

00:01:20.910 --> 00:01:22.770 align:middle line:10%
"Revelations of
the Ruby Crystal,"

00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:24.950 align:middle line:10%
and how that led
us into this story.

00:01:24.950 --> 00:01:25.950 align:middle line:10%
>> HAND CLOW: Let's see.

00:01:25.950 --> 00:01:29.120 align:middle line:10%
So at the end of "Ruby
Crystal," Armando

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:34.700 align:middle line:10%
has just met and fallen in love
with Jennifer, Simon's sister.

00:01:34.700 --> 00:01:37.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're
going to go over them

00:01:37.020 --> 00:01:38.160 align:middle line:90%
again-- the key characters.

00:01:38.160 --> 00:01:38.290 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yes.

00:01:38.290 --> 00:01:40.320 align:middle line:84%
So then when we go
into the second book,

00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:42.630 align:middle line:84%
this was the perfect
opportunity in a novel.

00:01:42.630 --> 00:01:45.450 align:middle line:84%
Because each novel has
to be a standalone.

00:01:45.450 --> 00:01:47.940 align:middle line:84%
So whenever new
character comes back,

00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.100 align:middle line:84%
you have to have the
background of that character--

00:01:50.100 --> 00:01:52.980 align:middle line:84%
not as much detail as in
the first book, of course.

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:55.410 align:middle line:84%
So that gave me the
opportunity to have

00:01:55.410 --> 00:01:57.880 align:middle line:84%
"Aquarian Age" begin with
the wedding of Jennifer

00:01:57.880 --> 00:01:58.680 align:middle line:90%
and Armando.

00:01:58.680 --> 00:02:00.570 align:middle line:84%
So the novel opens
with the wedding.

00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:02.790 align:middle line:84%
And then all of the characters
come to the wedding.

00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:03.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
and, of course, we

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:04.920 align:middle line:90%
love it, because it's in Italy.

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:05.330 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:02:05.330 --> 00:02:06.150 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Oh, yeah.

00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:07.560 align:middle line:84%
And also, as far
as I could tell,

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:10.139 align:middle line:84%
from talking to people who
had read "Ruby Crystal,"

00:02:10.139 --> 00:02:12.660 align:middle line:84%
they were just so happy to
have the characters back again.

00:02:12.660 --> 00:02:15.750 align:middle line:84%
Because people have become
fond of the characters.

00:02:15.750 --> 00:02:18.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's the goal, as
far as I'm concerned.

00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:20.940 align:middle line:84%
Everybody has different
ideas about fiction.

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:23.880 align:middle line:84%
But I think the most important
thing is the characters.

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:27.840 align:middle line:84%
Because when you read complex
material or information

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:32.190 align:middle line:84%
about a historical era, if you
do it through characterization,

00:02:32.190 --> 00:02:34.390 align:middle line:84%
the people who read
the book remember.

00:02:34.390 --> 00:02:35.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It brings
the emotions in.

00:02:35.890 --> 00:02:39.910 align:middle line:84%
It brings in more
multi-dimensional memory,

00:02:39.910 --> 00:02:40.710 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:02:40.710 --> 00:02:41.250 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:42.000 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.416 align:middle line:84%
And so that's one
of the reasons I

00:02:43.416 --> 00:02:46.662 align:middle line:84%
wanted to write fiction was
to have that extra kick.

00:02:46.662 --> 00:02:48.120 align:middle line:84%
And when you think
about it, if you

00:02:48.120 --> 00:02:52.110 align:middle line:84%
read a history of England,
English kings or whatever,

00:02:52.110 --> 00:02:53.680 align:middle line:90%
you can't remember anything.

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:56.490 align:middle line:84%
But then once you read of a
fictional rendition of one

00:02:56.490 --> 00:02:59.490 align:middle line:84%
of those kings or
queen's life, you

00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:00.930 align:middle line:90%
remember it forever, basically.

00:03:00.930 --> 00:03:02.471 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Absolutely--
and especially

00:03:02.471 --> 00:03:05.040 align:middle line:10%
if it's taken to the big
screen even more so, where

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:07.020 align:middle line:10%
you have music
driving the emotions

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:08.420 align:middle line:10%
and driving the points in.

00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:09.253 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Right.

00:03:09.253 --> 00:03:11.980 align:middle line:84%
And so my goal here was
to bring in some material

00:03:11.980 --> 00:03:13.880 align:middle line:84%
at the end of the
"Age of Pisces"

00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:17.340 align:middle line:84%
and going into "Aquarius"
that's truly significant for us,

00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:18.450 align:middle line:90%
as readers.

00:03:18.450 --> 00:03:21.400 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why I wanted
to create these characters.

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.880 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't actually create
the characters, Regina.

00:03:23.880 --> 00:03:26.400 align:middle line:90%
They all came in one day.

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.200 align:middle line:90%
May of 2011, they all came in.

00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:30.340 align:middle line:84%
And all I did was take
out my yellow pad.

00:03:30.340 --> 00:03:31.140 align:middle line:90%
And I wrote.

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:34.000 align:middle line:84%
What came in was their names,
their ages, their careers,

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:35.660 align:middle line:90%
their psychology.

00:03:35.660 --> 00:03:38.070 align:middle line:84%
And so they all came
in, except for one.

00:03:38.070 --> 00:03:39.630 align:middle line:90%
And one came in later.

00:03:39.630 --> 00:03:41.910 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know where
they came from exactly.

00:03:41.910 --> 00:03:44.070 align:middle line:84%
But they sure do
want to speak to us.

00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:45.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:47.550 align:middle line:90%
It's a story that is trying to--

00:03:47.550 --> 00:03:49.320 align:middle line:90%
in a difficult time--

00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:51.270 align:middle line:84%
tell us about some
of the dysfunction

00:03:51.270 --> 00:03:54.370 align:middle line:84%
in the darkness that's been
hidden from humanity up

00:03:54.370 --> 00:03:55.170 align:middle line:90%
until now.

00:03:55.170 --> 00:03:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Which is now all the
whistleblowers are out,

00:03:56.610 --> 00:03:57.540 align:middle line:90%
and it's happening.

00:03:57.540 --> 00:04:01.980 align:middle line:84%
But still, I don't think
people have any understanding

00:04:01.980 --> 00:04:04.740 align:middle line:84%
of how ubiquitous one
of the problems that

00:04:04.740 --> 00:04:05.970 align:middle line:90%
is demonstrated here is.

00:04:05.970 --> 00:04:07.950 align:middle line:84%
And we'll get into that
when the time comes.

00:04:07.950 --> 00:04:09.750 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, the
interesting part is

00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:11.670 align:middle line:84%
that these characters,
each one of them,

00:04:11.670 --> 00:04:15.030 align:middle line:84%
is brilliant and has their
own area of expertise, which

00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:18.720 align:middle line:84%
allows them to introduce
different pieces of history

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:21.245 align:middle line:84%
and psychology
into the storyline.

00:04:21.245 --> 00:04:22.620 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW:
Yeah, that's right.

00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:24.934 align:middle line:84%
And then, also, two
generations, too--

00:04:24.934 --> 00:04:26.850 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have that
perspective of the older

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:30.770 align:middle line:84%
generation dealing with people
who were in their 30s and 40s

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:32.470 align:middle line:84%
and coping with
the level of change

00:04:32.470 --> 00:04:34.470 align:middle line:84%
that we're experiencing
on the planet right now.

00:04:34.470 --> 00:04:36.200 align:middle line:84%
So that's why there's
two generations.

00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:37.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
technically three.

00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:38.430 align:middle line:84%
Because you've got a
little one in there, too--

00:04:38.430 --> 00:04:39.540 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: We've got
a little one coming.

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:41.081 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --that is
also exemplifying

00:04:41.081 --> 00:04:45.090 align:middle line:84%
the new consciousness, the super
sensitivity of the little ones

00:04:45.090 --> 00:04:47.920 align:middle line:84%
that are coming in this
particular energy field.

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:51.090 align:middle line:84%
OK, so you mentioned
Armando a little while ago.

00:04:51.090 --> 00:04:56.030 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about Armando, who
is one of the chief characters.

00:04:56.030 --> 00:04:59.460 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
comes up-- because this book

00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:02.790 align:middle line:84%
has areas of extreme
passion even sexuality.

00:05:02.790 --> 00:05:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Because again, that's
a part of our nature

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:07.190 align:middle line:90%
that's been severely repressed.

00:05:07.190 --> 00:05:10.230 align:middle line:84%
And Armando, in
this story, is being

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:15.690 align:middle line:84%
driven by a reptilian kind of
urge that moves through him.

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:20.380 align:middle line:84%
So let's set Armando up in
this aspect of his being.

00:05:20.380 --> 00:05:23.840 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Armando is a key
player right in "Ruby Crystal."

00:05:23.840 --> 00:05:26.600 align:middle line:84%
And when the issue
of Armando came up,

00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:27.990 align:middle line:84%
I talked to my
daughter about it.

00:05:27.990 --> 00:05:29.597 align:middle line:90%
Because I said, Lizzie--

00:05:29.597 --> 00:05:31.180 align:middle line:84%
Lizzie is the
illustrator of the book.

00:05:31.180 --> 00:05:31.550 align:middle line:90%
So we can bring--

00:05:31.550 --> 00:05:32.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Beautiful
illustrations.

00:05:32.050 --> 00:05:33.740 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: --Lizzie
into this conversation.

00:05:33.740 --> 00:05:36.230 align:middle line:84%
So I said Lizzie, this is
what's going on with Armando.

00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:38.620 align:middle line:84%
And Lizzie knows what
a nice person I am.

00:05:38.620 --> 00:05:42.522 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a well-adjusted wife,
and mother, and member of my--

00:05:42.522 --> 00:05:43.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're a nice girl.

00:05:43.730 --> 00:05:45.390 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: I'm
just a nice girl.

00:05:45.390 --> 00:05:46.610 align:middle line:90%
And Lizzie said, OK, Mom.

00:05:46.610 --> 00:05:47.720 align:middle line:90%
And Lizzie's a Scorpio.

00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:49.670 align:middle line:84%
And so Lizzie said,
no matter what you do,

00:05:49.670 --> 00:05:51.830 align:middle line:90%
Mom, make it really bad.

00:05:51.830 --> 00:05:53.650 align:middle line:90%
So I followed her advice.

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:55.550 align:middle line:84%
I probably didn't need
to know that from her.

00:05:55.550 --> 00:05:58.460 align:middle line:84%
Because Armando, just for
me from the very beginning,

00:05:58.460 --> 00:06:01.090 align:middle line:90%
was really a real person.

00:06:01.090 --> 00:06:02.910 align:middle line:84%
And so in the
first book, Armando

00:06:02.910 --> 00:06:05.090 align:middle line:90%
is a very, very bad guy.

00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:07.410 align:middle line:84%
And then he goes
through a lot of therapy

00:06:07.410 --> 00:06:10.100 align:middle line:84%
and comes to another
level, finally to the point

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:12.500 align:middle line:84%
where he's able, 10 years
after a lot of therapy,

00:06:12.500 --> 00:06:16.040 align:middle line:84%
to actually meet a woman
and end up marrying her.

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And so the other thing that's
fascinating about Armando

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.590 align:middle line:90%
is Armando was a painter.

00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:24.860 align:middle line:84%
And Armando has a
fantastic ability

00:06:24.860 --> 00:06:27.590 align:middle line:84%
to bring forces, and
energy, and archetypes

00:06:27.590 --> 00:06:30.780 align:middle line:84%
through his consciousness
and then paint.

00:06:30.780 --> 00:06:33.349 align:middle line:84%
And so I've had a lot of
fun describing painting

00:06:33.349 --> 00:06:34.640 align:middle line:90%
and what happens with painting.

00:06:34.640 --> 00:06:37.220 align:middle line:84%
Because I don't think it's
dealt with enough in literature.

00:06:37.220 --> 00:06:37.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's not.

00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:39.835 align:middle line:84%
And it's a real central
theme in the book, as well,

00:06:39.835 --> 00:06:41.990 align:middle line:90%
this one particular painting.

00:06:41.990 --> 00:06:46.070 align:middle line:84%
But he has these other darker
urges that move through him,

00:06:46.070 --> 00:06:49.640 align:middle line:84%
and these incredible,
light-filled, unconscious

00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:53.000 align:middle line:84%
understandings that
just appear in his work.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:56.360 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about that
confluence of these parts

00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:57.740 align:middle line:90%
in his being.

00:06:57.740 --> 00:06:59.900 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah, well
he, himself personally,

00:06:59.900 --> 00:07:02.990 align:middle line:84%
is struggling with a force
that I consider to be the force

00:07:02.990 --> 00:07:03.830 align:middle line:90%
of the Archons.

00:07:03.830 --> 00:07:05.870 align:middle line:10%
This is a force
that's been identified

00:07:05.870 --> 00:07:09.620 align:middle line:10%
by John Lash,
which is definitely

00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:11.670 align:middle line:10%
a very reptilian force.

00:07:11.670 --> 00:07:15.220 align:middle line:10%
And so in his case, he comes
from a very good family.

00:07:15.220 --> 00:07:17.870 align:middle line:84%
And until he was sexually
abused when he was young,

00:07:17.870 --> 00:07:20.360 align:middle line:84%
he was a very, very
happy little boy.

00:07:20.360 --> 00:07:22.460 align:middle line:84%
So he's having a
tremendous struggle

00:07:22.460 --> 00:07:26.120 align:middle line:84%
with forces running through him
that he does not want to have.

00:07:26.120 --> 00:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
He does not want to be
that kind of person.

00:07:28.310 --> 00:07:32.540 align:middle line:84%
And so then, he resolves
dealing with these forces going

00:07:32.540 --> 00:07:34.340 align:middle line:90%
through him by painting.

00:07:34.340 --> 00:07:36.130 align:middle line:84%
And so when we see
him painting and when

00:07:36.130 --> 00:07:37.970 align:middle line:84%
we see him becoming
an artist, that's

00:07:37.970 --> 00:07:40.820 align:middle line:84%
when we see this light
coming through him.

00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:42.790 align:middle line:84%
Because it's right
there within him.

00:07:42.790 --> 00:07:46.240 align:middle line:84%
But he's having this
tremendous personal struggle.

00:07:46.240 --> 00:07:50.280 align:middle line:84%
The main issue of this
trilogy is, how does evil

00:07:50.280 --> 00:07:51.910 align:middle line:90%
get into the world?

00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:54.900 align:middle line:84%
In other words, evil is a real
force, as far as we can tell.

00:07:54.900 --> 00:07:56.910 align:middle line:84%
But how does it
get into our world?

00:07:56.910 --> 00:08:00.810 align:middle line:84%
Because if we could understand
how evil comes into our world,

00:08:00.810 --> 00:08:02.460 align:middle line:84%
then, surely, we'd
have some ways

00:08:02.460 --> 00:08:07.830 align:middle line:84%
of transmuting it using therapy,
whatever we would choose to do.

00:08:07.830 --> 00:08:10.410 align:middle line:84%
But when I first started
this trilogy back in 2011,

00:08:10.410 --> 00:08:13.990 align:middle line:84%
it was only just beginning to be
clear what a big deal this is.

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:15.720 align:middle line:84%
And now it's getting
bigger and bigger.

00:08:15.720 --> 00:08:17.340 align:middle line:84%
Because something
is actually going

00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:20.430 align:middle line:84%
on within systems of the
church that are actually

00:08:20.430 --> 00:08:22.290 align:middle line:90%
creating these events.

00:08:22.290 --> 00:08:25.500 align:middle line:10%
And I personally feel
that Pope Francis

00:08:25.500 --> 00:08:26.950 align:middle line:10%
is very concerned about this.

00:08:26.950 --> 00:08:30.210 align:middle line:10%
And I actually feel that he's
really trying to change things.

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:31.542 align:middle line:10%
But he's having a big struggle.

00:08:31.542 --> 00:08:33.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He's having a big
struggle himself with it.

00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Because it is such it's
stayed institution.

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:39.120 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: It's a
1,500-year creation.

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.640 align:middle line:84%
To root that out, it's
an Earth-shattering and

00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:44.230 align:middle line:84%
psyche-shattering
experience for children.

00:08:44.230 --> 00:08:47.160 align:middle line:84%
And so in the book,
Armando isn't the only one

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:49.980 align:middle line:90%
in dealing with other people--

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:51.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And secrecy around it.

00:08:51.340 --> 00:08:51.510 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Right.

00:08:51.510 --> 00:08:54.090 align:middle line:84%
And showing, also, what
happened in their childhood

00:08:54.090 --> 00:08:56.310 align:middle line:84%
and in their early
adulthood as a result

00:08:56.310 --> 00:08:57.720 align:middle line:90%
of having been sexually abused.

00:08:57.720 --> 00:09:00.000 align:middle line:84%
And I was sexually
abused when I was two

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:01.500 align:middle line:90%
and a half to three years old.

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And I don't mind saying that,
because I wrote about it.

00:09:04.260 --> 00:09:06.720 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a trilogy called "The
Mind Chronicles Trilogy."

00:09:06.720 --> 00:09:08.040 align:middle line:90%
And I've already revealed that.

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:10.110 align:middle line:84%
And so I've gone
through this experience

00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:13.830 align:middle line:84%
personally and somehow
managed to get beyond it.

00:09:13.830 --> 00:09:17.901 align:middle line:84%
I sometimes wonder, who was
the angel that kept me going

00:09:17.901 --> 00:09:19.650 align:middle line:84%
and helped me go all
the way through this?

00:09:19.650 --> 00:09:21.420 align:middle line:84%
Because I made it
all the way through.

00:09:21.420 --> 00:09:24.480 align:middle line:84%
But I do feel that I have
unusual understanding

00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:26.010 align:middle line:90%
of this issue.

00:09:26.010 --> 00:09:29.460 align:middle line:84%
And then in my 30s, I almost
became a Jungian analyst.

00:09:29.460 --> 00:09:31.080 align:middle line:90%
I actually did some training.

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:33.240 align:middle line:84%
And so there there's a
character in the book,

00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:36.476 align:middle line:84%
a wonderful character,
Lorenzo Giannini.

00:09:36.476 --> 00:09:37.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love him.

00:09:37.350 --> 00:09:37.700 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah, I know.

00:09:37.700 --> 00:09:38.982 align:middle line:90%
I love Lorenzo.

00:09:38.982 --> 00:09:40.440 align:middle line:84%
He gets in the
third book, Regina--

00:09:40.440 --> 00:09:42.314 align:middle line:84%
which, as you know, I'm
writing it right now.

00:09:42.314 --> 00:09:43.530 align:middle line:90%
The first two are published.

00:09:43.530 --> 00:09:45.660 align:middle line:90%
And I'm writing the third one.

00:09:45.660 --> 00:09:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And Lorenzo ends up just
being a kingpin in the middle

00:09:48.330 --> 00:09:49.320 align:middle line:90%
of everybody's lives.

00:09:49.320 --> 00:09:51.819 align:middle line:84%
Because gradually, they
all start going to him.

00:09:51.819 --> 00:09:52.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: As a therapist.

00:09:52.860 --> 00:09:53.660 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:09:53.660 --> 00:09:55.860 align:middle line:84%
And so having almost
become a Jungian analyst,

00:09:55.860 --> 00:09:57.690 align:middle line:84%
I've had the
wonderful opportunity

00:09:57.690 --> 00:09:59.980 align:middle line:84%
to have a Jungian
analyst in literature.

00:09:59.980 --> 00:10:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Because then, as
a reader, we get

00:10:02.200 --> 00:10:05.590 align:middle line:84%
to peek into what's going on
in these analytic sessions

00:10:05.590 --> 00:10:06.390 align:middle line:90%
with clients.

00:10:06.390 --> 00:10:08.850 align:middle line:84%
And I just think that's
the most fascinating.

00:10:08.850 --> 00:10:10.359 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I agree
with you on that.

00:10:10.359 --> 00:10:12.900 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: I think all of us
would like to be able to peek

00:10:12.900 --> 00:10:14.640 align:middle line:84%
through a keyhole
and have an earpiece,

00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:16.016 align:middle line:84%
so we could hear
what's going on.

00:10:16.016 --> 00:10:18.181 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, he has a
kind of intuitive capacity,

00:10:18.181 --> 00:10:20.460 align:middle line:84%
too, where he can understand
when someone's coming up

00:10:20.460 --> 00:10:23.670 align:middle line:84%
on something and help them
look at it in a way that

00:10:23.670 --> 00:10:25.110 align:middle line:90%
might open even to past life.

00:10:25.110 --> 00:10:26.235 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:10:26.235 --> 00:10:30.000 align:middle line:10%
And then Lorenzo, like Carl Jung
himself, and many other Jungian

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:32.310 align:middle line:10%
analysts, is also a major Magus.

00:10:32.310 --> 00:10:34.590 align:middle line:10%
Many, many Jungian
analysts are highly

00:10:34.590 --> 00:10:37.350 align:middle line:10%
trained in psychic and
magical techniques.

00:10:37.350 --> 00:10:41.280 align:middle line:10%
And so Lorenzo is unusually
gifted in that way because

00:10:41.280 --> 00:10:43.230 align:middle line:10%
of training that he's
received himself.

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:44.580 align:middle line:90%
So he's not just an analyst.

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:47.880 align:middle line:90%
He's also a wonderful magician.

00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:50.280 align:middle line:90%
So go back to "Ruby Crystal."

00:10:50.280 --> 00:10:55.080 align:middle line:10%
When I started writing
"Ruby Crystal," Ratzinger

00:10:55.080 --> 00:10:56.430 align:middle line:10%
was the Pope--

00:10:56.430 --> 00:10:57.900 align:middle line:10%
Benedict the 16th.

00:10:57.900 --> 00:11:01.320 align:middle line:10%
And I knew I had a book
when Ratzinger resigned,

00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:02.670 align:middle line:10%
which was an amazing thing.

00:11:02.670 --> 00:11:04.810 align:middle line:84%
I'd written a third
of the first book.

00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:06.450 align:middle line:90%
And Ratzinger resigned.

00:11:06.450 --> 00:11:09.590 align:middle line:84%
And so then, of course,
Francis was elected.

00:11:09.590 --> 00:11:12.907 align:middle line:84%
And so through the third book--
the second book, of course,

00:11:12.907 --> 00:11:14.990 align:middle line:84%
is dealing with Francis a
little bit, as you know.

00:11:14.990 --> 00:11:17.340 align:middle line:84%
But the third book, I'm
going deeply into what's

00:11:17.340 --> 00:11:18.567 align:middle line:90%
really going on with Francis.

00:11:18.567 --> 00:11:19.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:20.608 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Oh, yeah.

00:11:20.608 --> 00:11:23.990 align:middle line:84%
Because at this point,
now we have data.

00:11:23.990 --> 00:11:25.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he's saying
things like, there has

00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:27.720 align:middle line:90%
been a real problem in Chile.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:31.650 align:middle line:84%
And he went down to Chile
and actually got himself

00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:32.700 align:middle line:90%
into a real mess.

00:11:32.700 --> 00:11:36.750 align:middle line:84%
Because he didn't support
some of the people in Chile

00:11:36.750 --> 00:11:39.690 align:middle line:84%
who had been abused by
a priest and a bishop.

00:11:39.690 --> 00:11:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And then what happened
after he didn't

00:11:42.180 --> 00:11:45.530 align:middle line:84%
support that particular
issue was the Chileans just--

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:46.530 align:middle line:90%
it was really wonderful.

00:11:46.530 --> 00:11:48.930 align:middle line:90%
They just rebelled en masse.

00:11:48.930 --> 00:11:55.610 align:middle line:84%
And then Francis sent in a
really fantastic investigator,

00:11:55.610 --> 00:11:58.020 align:middle line:84%
especially of bishops,
but of priestly abuse,

00:11:58.020 --> 00:12:01.260 align:middle line:84%
who happens to be the
archbishop from Malta.

00:12:01.260 --> 00:12:04.650 align:middle line:84%
And this is really interesting,
because Pietro Pierleoni, one

00:12:04.650 --> 00:12:07.260 align:middle line:84%
of the main characters all
the way through this trilogy,

00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:09.550 align:middle line:84%
is a member of the
order of Malta.

00:12:09.550 --> 00:12:12.010 align:middle line:84%
Now if I go back
it's five years ago--

00:12:12.010 --> 00:12:14.670 align:middle line:90%
and I basically go by guidance.

00:12:14.670 --> 00:12:17.850 align:middle line:84%
And the guidance told me that
Pietro was a major player

00:12:17.850 --> 00:12:19.360 align:middle line:90%
in the order of Malta.

00:12:19.360 --> 00:12:21.720 align:middle line:84%
I went, I don't think I'm
going to put this in the book.

00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:23.490 align:middle line:90%
What could this possibly mean?

00:12:23.490 --> 00:12:25.800 align:middle line:84%
Well, as it turns out,
there's a really big deal

00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:28.017 align:middle line:84%
going on with the Vatican
and the order of Malta.

00:12:28.017 --> 00:12:29.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What's going on?

00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:31.969 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Well, there
is an issue of finally--

00:12:31.969 --> 00:12:33.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Really cracking down.

00:12:33.260 --> 00:12:35.490 align:middle line:10%
>> HAND CLOW: Well, Francis
sent in the investigator,

00:12:35.490 --> 00:12:37.830 align:middle line:10%
this archbishop from Malta,
because he knew that he was

00:12:37.830 --> 00:12:40.020 align:middle line:10%
the most hardcore investigator.

00:12:40.020 --> 00:12:43.290 align:middle line:10%
And this archbishop went in.

00:12:43.290 --> 00:12:47.040 align:middle line:10%
And so he went and investigated
the situation in Chile

00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:48.620 align:middle line:10%
and came back to
Francis and said,

00:12:48.620 --> 00:12:50.400 align:middle line:10%
OK, Francis, here's the deal.

00:12:50.400 --> 00:12:53.830 align:middle line:84%
He gave him the 2,300-page
report on what was going

00:12:53.830 --> 00:12:54.850 align:middle line:90%
on in Chile.

00:12:54.850 --> 00:12:57.430 align:middle line:84%
And what's really incredible
to me and to everybody

00:12:57.430 --> 00:12:59.950 align:middle line:84%
else who's following what's
going on in the Vatican,

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:04.670 align:middle line:84%
Francis not only said, hey,
wait a minute, I blew this.

00:13:04.670 --> 00:13:08.140 align:middle line:84%
He not only said, I
didn't see, but he said,

00:13:08.140 --> 00:13:11.330 align:middle line:84%
I now know that
I've been misguided.

00:13:11.330 --> 00:13:14.140 align:middle line:84%
And then the Pope
said, and I know

00:13:14.140 --> 00:13:16.450 align:middle line:84%
that I'm part of the
problem, because I

00:13:16.450 --> 00:13:18.070 align:middle line:90%
couldn't see what's going on.

00:13:18.070 --> 00:13:19.694 align:middle line:90%
So this is such a huge turn--

00:13:19.694 --> 00:13:20.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What a revelation.

00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:23.080 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: And this is
only like two months ago.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:26.984 align:middle line:84%
And so as I'm the third
book, I write on a timeline.

00:13:26.984 --> 00:13:28.150 align:middle line:90%
That's what I do with these.

00:13:28.150 --> 00:13:29.480 align:middle line:90%
I write them on a timeline.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:32.299 align:middle line:84%
So when I'm writing, it's the
same time as when I'm writing.

00:13:32.299 --> 00:13:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And so this has already
started to come in.

00:13:34.090 --> 00:13:36.230 align:middle line:84%
And I have no idea
where it's going to go.

00:13:36.230 --> 00:13:37.390 align:middle line:90%
But I do know one thing.

00:13:37.390 --> 00:13:39.640 align:middle line:84%
This pope is going to make
a significant difference.

00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:41.350 align:middle line:84%
And probably because
we know that we're

00:13:41.350 --> 00:13:44.860 align:middle line:84%
at that point in time where
significant things are

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:45.662 align:middle line:90%
happening.

00:13:45.662 --> 00:13:47.120 align:middle line:84%
Things just aren't
getting stuffed.

00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:49.286 align:middle line:84%
And if you try to stuff it,
it doesn't work anymore.

00:13:49.286 --> 00:13:53.470 align:middle line:84%
Because you immediately
have an attack online.

00:13:53.470 --> 00:13:54.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:13:54.490 --> 00:13:54.890 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:13:54.890 --> 00:13:55.930 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: It's changing.

00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:56.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:13:56.730 --> 00:13:59.140 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting--
what you said

00:13:59.140 --> 00:14:00.790 align:middle line:84%
about garnering
American support,

00:14:00.790 --> 00:14:03.060 align:middle line:84%
so they keep money
flowing into the Vatican.

00:14:03.060 --> 00:14:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And in this documentary,
it was interesting,

00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:06.160 align:middle line:90%
because he's standing before--

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:07.480 align:middle line:90%
I think it was Congress.

00:14:07.480 --> 00:14:11.380 align:middle line:84%
And he was basically,
in his usual way,

00:14:11.380 --> 00:14:15.670 align:middle line:84%
chastising them
for funding weapons

00:14:15.670 --> 00:14:17.830 align:middle line:84%
to, quote, "rebels"
in the Middle East

00:14:17.830 --> 00:14:22.090 align:middle line:84%
and saying that, in order to
achieve our goals on Earth,

00:14:22.090 --> 00:14:23.337 align:middle line:90%
this must stop.

00:14:23.337 --> 00:14:24.420 align:middle line:90%
It was like, they're, hm--

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:24.730 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.396 align:middle line:84%
They didn't know quite
how to take that.

00:14:26.396 --> 00:14:30.250 align:middle line:84%
He does seem to be
sincerely trying

00:14:30.250 --> 00:14:33.520 align:middle line:84%
to draw attention to the
right things at this time,

00:14:33.520 --> 00:14:36.040 align:middle line:84%
even if his actions
have not yet fully been

00:14:36.040 --> 00:14:38.830 align:middle line:84%
made manifest to
address the problem.

00:14:38.830 --> 00:14:41.740 align:middle line:84%
So I bring it up, because this
is at the base of the story.

00:14:41.740 --> 00:14:44.620 align:middle line:84%
Secrecy around the
subject is at the base.

00:14:44.620 --> 00:14:47.360 align:middle line:84%
This incredible pain these
men have been living in

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:50.530 align:middle line:84%
is at the base of their
characters in this story.

00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:52.600 align:middle line:84%
Now let's go into some
of the historical parts.

00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:55.310 align:middle line:84%
Because you have Simon,
who is a journalist.

00:14:55.310 --> 00:14:58.490 align:middle line:84%
You have all these beautiful
academic women, as well.

00:14:58.490 --> 00:15:03.670 align:middle line:84%
And they bring in the story
of the ancient Mandaeans,

00:15:03.670 --> 00:15:05.246 align:middle line:90%
