lot of implications.

00:26:28.370 --> 00:26:31.840 align:middle line:84%
Now you talk about the book
in the book you've written.

00:26:31.840 --> 00:26:33.130 align:middle line:90%
This does come up.

00:26:33.130 --> 00:26:36.700 align:middle line:84%
But why don't you just go
ahead and give the viewers

00:26:36.700 --> 00:26:39.830 align:middle line:84%
a snippet of the significance
of this particular book?

00:26:39.830 --> 00:26:40.630 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:26:40.630 --> 00:26:42.940 align:middle line:84%
This is a very
significant theme.

00:26:42.940 --> 00:26:46.090 align:middle line:84%
The theme is the
issue of the discovery

00:26:46.090 --> 00:26:50.420 align:middle line:84%
of the family tomb of the
family of Jesus back in 1980.

00:26:50.420 --> 00:26:54.760 align:middle line:84%
And one of the reasons the book
is mentioned is, in the novels,

00:26:54.760 --> 00:26:57.600 align:middle line:84%
whenever I actually really
cover significant research

00:26:57.600 --> 00:27:01.000 align:middle line:84%
by a person, I always like
to acknowledge people.

00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.990 align:middle line:84%
So one of my characters
just said, hey,

00:27:02.990 --> 00:27:04.840 align:middle line:84%
you got to read that
book, because it

00:27:04.840 --> 00:27:05.790 align:middle line:90%
says blah, blah, blah.

00:27:05.790 --> 00:27:08.080 align:middle line:84%
So that's why we're
talking about the book.

00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:10.000 align:middle line:84%
But the theme behind
it, which is actually

00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:14.920 align:middle line:84%
the work of other authors
besides Simcha Jacobovici--

00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:16.200 align:middle line:90%
it's a hard name.

00:27:16.200 --> 00:27:17.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:27:17.030 --> 00:27:18.690 align:middle line:84%
That's why I didn't
try to say it.

00:27:18.690 --> 00:27:19.090 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:27:19.090 --> 00:27:20.640 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: And
then James Cameron,

00:27:20.640 --> 00:27:25.700 align:middle line:84%
the director of "Avatar," made
a film with Simcha Jacobovici,

00:27:25.700 --> 00:27:29.740 align:middle line:84%
which viewers may have seen
back in 2007 called "The Jesus

00:27:29.740 --> 00:27:32.650 align:middle line:84%
Family Tomb," where they
actually went down with cameras

00:27:32.650 --> 00:27:34.270 align:middle line:90%
and went into the tomb.

00:27:34.270 --> 00:27:36.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, the reason this is
such a significant theme--

00:27:36.790 --> 00:27:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yet, almost
no one heard about it.

00:27:39.760 --> 00:27:42.410 align:middle line:84%
Whenever I talk to people,
they say, what film?

00:27:42.410 --> 00:27:43.210 align:middle line:90%
What book?

00:27:43.210 --> 00:27:43.540 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:27:43.540 --> 00:27:45.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is an
interesting thing.

00:27:45.010 --> 00:27:47.700 align:middle line:84%
Because one of the
things that I love doing

00:27:47.700 --> 00:27:50.340 align:middle line:84%
is finding something
that's really significant

00:27:50.340 --> 00:27:52.770 align:middle line:84%
and then noticing that,
even though a whole lot

00:27:52.770 --> 00:27:56.070 align:middle line:84%
of other people hear about
it, it immediately goes blank.

00:27:56.070 --> 00:27:59.100 align:middle line:84%
Because when people hear
something that goes radically

00:27:59.100 --> 00:28:01.740 align:middle line:84%
against what they've always
been taught to believe,

00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:04.054 align:middle line:90%
their brains tend to go blank.

00:28:04.054 --> 00:28:05.970 align:middle line:84%
So the reason there's a
big blank on this one,

00:28:05.970 --> 00:28:07.928 align:middle line:84%
even though there's been
actually a huge amount

00:28:07.928 --> 00:28:10.740 align:middle line:84%
of publicity about
it, is that people

00:28:10.740 --> 00:28:14.550 align:middle line:84%
have been so trained to
believe in the Resurrection.

00:28:14.550 --> 00:28:15.480 align:middle line:90%
That's what happened.

00:28:15.480 --> 00:28:17.637 align:middle line:84%
When Jesus died, he
got resurrected, right?

00:28:17.637 --> 00:28:19.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, the only problem
is, there was a tomb.

00:28:19.470 --> 00:28:21.510 align:middle line:90%
And his body was in it.

00:28:21.510 --> 00:28:24.540 align:middle line:84%
His wife, Mary
Magdalene, the body

00:28:24.540 --> 00:28:26.790 align:middle line:84%
of a child named Judah, who
was probably their son--

00:28:26.790 --> 00:28:27.135 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Brother.

00:28:27.135 --> 00:28:28.470 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Brothers, that's
right-- a lot of people,

00:28:28.470 --> 00:28:29.400 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:28:29.400 --> 00:28:31.560 align:middle line:90%
Jesus had seven siblings.

00:28:31.560 --> 00:28:35.010 align:middle line:84%
And all kinds of people
think that Jesus didn't

00:28:35.010 --> 00:28:36.330 align:middle line:90%
have any brothers or sisters.

00:28:36.330 --> 00:28:38.010 align:middle line:84%
Because of course,
his mother, Mary,

00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:40.600 align:middle line:90%
couldn't have possibly had sex.

00:28:40.600 --> 00:28:42.930 align:middle line:84%
So there's this immaculate
conception still going on.

00:28:42.930 --> 00:28:44.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Couldn't have had
seven immaculate conceptions.

00:28:44.120 --> 00:28:44.360 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:28:44.360 --> 00:28:45.160 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:28:45.160 --> 00:28:47.160 align:middle line:84%
So what happened basically
is-- the real story

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:50.040 align:middle line:84%
is Jesus was a real person
and a really fine person,

00:28:50.040 --> 00:28:51.210 align:middle line:90%
as far as I can tell.

00:28:51.210 --> 00:28:53.310 align:middle line:90%
A whole man, a father--

00:28:53.310 --> 00:28:55.950 align:middle line:84%
why can't a great spiritual
teacher be a father

00:28:55.950 --> 00:28:58.361 align:middle line:90%
and be a husband, after all?

00:28:58.361 --> 00:28:59.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Good question.

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:00.750 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Well, why not?

00:29:00.750 --> 00:29:04.860 align:middle line:84%
I admire a person more when they
have a really beautiful family

00:29:04.860 --> 00:29:07.570 align:middle line:90%
life, as well as their teaching.

00:29:07.570 --> 00:29:10.470 align:middle line:84%
So the tomb was
discovered in 1980.

00:29:10.470 --> 00:29:13.410 align:middle line:84%
There's been a huge
attempt by the Vatican

00:29:13.410 --> 00:29:17.190 align:middle line:84%
and by the Jewish antiquities
authorities to cover this up.

00:29:17.190 --> 00:29:19.050 align:middle line:84%
But there's so much
evidence that's

00:29:19.050 --> 00:29:20.650 align:middle line:90%
been established and proven.

00:29:20.650 --> 00:29:23.470 align:middle line:84%
And if people want
to read my novels,

00:29:23.470 --> 00:29:26.070 align:middle line:84%
they may want to pick up
some of this information

00:29:26.070 --> 00:29:27.990 align:middle line:84%
and start digging
more deeply in it.

00:29:27.990 --> 00:29:30.615 align:middle line:84%
Because all I can do is present
characters who talk about this.

00:29:30.615 --> 00:29:32.739 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's why
I wanted to bring it up.

00:29:32.739 --> 00:29:34.350 align:middle line:84%
Maybe some people
can get a jump on it

00:29:34.350 --> 00:29:36.489 align:middle line:84%
before even the
third book comes out.

00:29:36.489 --> 00:29:37.530 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah, yeah.

00:29:37.530 --> 00:29:42.300 align:middle line:84%
And this may be, possibly,
one of the greatest

00:29:42.300 --> 00:29:44.770 align:middle line:84%
archaeological discoveries
of the last 100 years.

00:29:44.770 --> 00:29:45.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:29:45.570 --> 00:29:47.370 align:middle line:84%
Now we can understand
why the Vatican church

00:29:47.370 --> 00:29:48.453 align:middle line:90%
would want to cover it up.

00:29:48.453 --> 00:29:50.790 align:middle line:84%
But why would the Israeli
Department of Antiquities

00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:51.770 align:middle line:90%
want to cover it up?

00:29:51.770 --> 00:29:53.811 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Now that is
a complicated question,

00:29:53.811 --> 00:29:57.100 align:middle line:84%
which I could give
you a long answer.

00:29:57.100 --> 00:29:58.950 align:middle line:84%
But I think it
would be too long.

00:29:58.950 --> 00:30:03.720 align:middle line:84%
But the Jewish authorities, just
like Christians authorities--

00:30:03.720 --> 00:30:05.850 align:middle line:90%
they also have a fairy story--

00:30:05.850 --> 00:30:08.160 align:middle line:84%
for example, things
like the Exodus.

00:30:08.160 --> 00:30:09.160 align:middle line:90%
It's not true.

00:30:09.160 --> 00:30:10.670 align:middle line:90%
It's just a fairy story.

00:30:10.670 --> 00:30:13.890 align:middle line:84%
And so when things come
up archaeologically,

00:30:13.890 --> 00:30:17.910 align:middle line:84%
when discoveries are made that
go against a prevailing fairy

00:30:17.910 --> 00:30:20.260 align:middle line:90%
story, people start fighting it.

00:30:20.260 --> 00:30:22.980 align:middle line:84%
But the reasons that the
Jews have been hiding this

00:30:22.980 --> 00:30:24.400 align:middle line:90%
are very complex.

00:30:24.400 --> 00:30:28.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So moving on
from Jacobovici's work,

00:30:28.160 --> 00:30:31.725 align:middle line:84%
we go back to the story and
Armando and this painting

00:30:31.725 --> 00:30:32.850 align:middle line:90%
that's flowing through him.

00:30:32.850 --> 00:30:36.090 align:middle line:84%
He's obsessed with doing
this painting, which becomes

00:30:36.090 --> 00:30:38.980 align:middle line:90%
a big revelation at the end.

00:30:38.980 --> 00:30:43.200 align:middle line:84%
And it really has to do
with the sacred union that's

00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:46.620 align:middle line:84%
flowing through him and the
need for this sacred union--

00:30:46.620 --> 00:30:49.000 align:middle line:84%
again, what we were
talking about earlier.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:49.800 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:30:49.800 --> 00:30:50.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, imagine this.

00:30:50.630 --> 00:30:54.810 align:middle line:10%
He was a big Roman and
European famous painter,

00:30:54.810 --> 00:30:57.210 align:middle line:10%
mostly famous for
painting triptyches,

00:30:57.210 --> 00:30:59.940 align:middle line:10%
with the Upper World, the Middle
World, and Lower World in them,

00:30:59.940 --> 00:31:00.610 align:middle line:10%
like we see in--

00:31:00.610 --> 00:31:01.485 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Like Dante.

00:31:01.485 --> 00:31:03.550 align:middle line:10%
>> HAND CLOW: --Medieval
art like Dante, exactly.

00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:06.630 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly, he couldn't
paint his normal painting

00:31:06.630 --> 00:31:07.500 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:31:07.500 --> 00:31:11.250 align:middle line:84%
And he just became obsessed with
bringing through this image.

00:31:11.250 --> 00:31:13.050 align:middle line:84%
And then it's
described in detail

00:31:13.050 --> 00:31:15.450 align:middle line:84%
how he does it, which
is really fascinating.

00:31:15.450 --> 00:31:20.220 align:middle line:84%
But it's an image of Mary
Magdalene on the ground

00:31:20.220 --> 00:31:23.580 align:middle line:84%
and reaching up for Christ,
who is basically ascending.

00:31:23.580 --> 00:31:25.920 align:middle line:90%
He's on the verge of taking off.

00:31:25.920 --> 00:31:30.780 align:middle line:84%
And basically, what happens
further on in the novel is

00:31:30.780 --> 00:31:33.480 align:middle line:84%
it becomes clearer that the
people who see this painting

00:31:33.480 --> 00:31:35.970 align:middle line:84%
experience the real
presence of Christ.

00:31:35.970 --> 00:31:38.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's always been an
issue in Catholic religion,

00:31:38.790 --> 00:31:40.955 align:middle line:84%
Christian religion, through
actual, real Christ.

00:31:40.955 --> 00:31:43.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But it was also
through this entanglement

00:31:43.080 --> 00:31:44.220 align:middle line:90%
of love with this woman.

00:31:44.220 --> 00:31:46.110 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Well,
that's how it turns out.

00:31:46.110 --> 00:31:49.500 align:middle line:84%
And as it turns out, his
version of the real presence

00:31:49.500 --> 00:31:52.775 align:middle line:84%
involves him being in
love with his wife.

00:31:52.775 --> 00:31:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And so this is a whole
big shift in the meaning

00:31:56.460 --> 00:31:57.680 align:middle line:90%
of the real presence.

00:31:57.680 --> 00:32:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a major theme,
of course, going all the way

00:32:00.310 --> 00:32:01.110 align:middle line:90%
through the book.

00:32:01.110 --> 00:32:05.220 align:middle line:84%
And the interesting thing about
that to me-- now, here I am.

00:32:05.220 --> 00:32:08.010 align:middle line:90%
I write on the timeline.

00:32:08.010 --> 00:32:12.000 align:middle line:84%
Like, if it's June 2014,
what's going on outside

00:32:12.000 --> 00:32:14.760 align:middle line:84%
the characters is
on the timeline.

00:32:14.760 --> 00:32:19.080 align:middle line:84%
So just exactly when Armando was
able to execute that painting

00:32:19.080 --> 00:32:23.670 align:middle line:84%
and bring it in,
a amazing painting

00:32:23.670 --> 00:32:26.730 align:middle line:84%
appeared on the world scene
called "Salvador Mundi"

00:32:26.730 --> 00:32:28.650 align:middle line:90%
by Leonardo da Vinci.

00:32:28.650 --> 00:32:32.940 align:middle line:84%
And this is a painting of Christ
that was finally authenticated

00:32:32.940 --> 00:32:36.430 align:middle line:84%
after 500 years of arguing about
whether it's really Leonardo

00:32:36.430 --> 00:32:37.230 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:32:37.230 --> 00:32:39.210 align:middle line:84%
So finally, it
was authenticated.

00:32:39.210 --> 00:32:42.240 align:middle line:84%
And a Saudi prince fought
it for $45 million.

00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, the world was
able to see this painting.

00:32:45.990 --> 00:32:48.360 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I
saw images of it.

00:32:48.360 --> 00:32:51.566 align:middle line:84%
And it's just absolutely the
most astonishing painting.

00:32:51.566 --> 00:32:52.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Tell us about it.

00:32:52.690 --> 00:32:55.480 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: What it is is
just simply the face of Christ.

00:32:55.480 --> 00:32:58.650 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at it, you
can see all of the dimensions

00:32:58.650 --> 00:33:02.910 align:middle line:84%
and all of the cosmic realms
relating to his image.

00:33:02.910 --> 00:33:04.500 align:middle line:90%
It's incredible.

00:33:04.500 --> 00:33:07.830 align:middle line:84%
But it came in just when
Armando's painting came in.

00:33:07.830 --> 00:33:09.450 align:middle line:84%
And I have been
having this experience

00:33:09.450 --> 00:33:11.580 align:middle line:84%
all the way through
the trilogy of things

00:33:11.580 --> 00:33:13.552 align:middle line:84%
happening as I'm
writing that actually--

00:33:13.552 --> 00:33:14.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You get a download.

00:33:14.760 --> 00:33:17.740 align:middle line:84%
And then this shows up in the
international arena somewhere.

00:33:17.740 --> 00:33:18.540 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:33:18.540 --> 00:33:20.373 align:middle line:84%
In other words, there's
some kind of pick-up

00:33:20.373 --> 00:33:21.520 align:middle line:90%
that I'm having.

00:33:21.520 --> 00:33:23.515 align:middle line:90%
I pick things up that way.

00:33:23.515 --> 00:33:25.200 align:middle line:90%
That's how actually I trust.

00:33:25.200 --> 00:33:27.270 align:middle line:84%
Because as I'm in
the third book now,

00:33:27.270 --> 00:33:30.180 align:middle line:84%
the degree to which I have
to trust is really intense.

00:33:30.180 --> 00:33:33.300 align:middle line:84%
Because now I'm really dealing
with complicated material.

00:33:33.300 --> 00:33:36.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You are Yes.

00:33:36.420 --> 00:33:38.850 align:middle line:84%
Well, OK, so now passing
on from what you just

00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:41.640 align:middle line:84%
talked about and this
painting that Armando's done,

00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:46.620 align:middle line:84%
there is a position in the
book that matrimonial sects

00:33:46.620 --> 00:33:47.985 align:middle line:90%
has a redemptive quality.

00:33:47.985 --> 00:33:49.110 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:33:49.110 --> 00:33:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And talk about
this for a little bit.

00:33:51.100 --> 00:33:51.900 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:33:51.900 --> 00:33:54.870 align:middle line:84%
At the same time in the middle
of all this stuff coming

00:33:54.870 --> 00:33:58.280 align:middle line:84%
through, a book has
come through called--

00:33:58.280 --> 00:34:01.620 align:middle line:84%
it's a book based
on a manuscript that

00:34:01.620 --> 00:34:03.690 align:middle line:84%
was written in the
first or second century

00:34:03.690 --> 00:34:06.990 align:middle line:90%
AD called "Joseph and Aseneth."

00:34:06.990 --> 00:34:11.199 align:middle line:84%
And this stuff is
really complicated.

00:34:11.199 --> 00:34:14.520 align:middle line:84%
But it's not that
complicated in the book.

00:34:14.520 --> 00:34:15.948 align:middle line:90%
The characters just simply say--

00:34:15.948 --> 00:34:17.489 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Not in
your book, it's not.

00:34:17.489 --> 00:34:18.289 align:middle line:90%
>> HAND CLOW: No.

00:34:18.289 --> 00:34:21.000 align:middle line:84%
The characters simply say, I
heard this had been translated.

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:26.130 align:middle line:84%
And Sarah Appel is a
patristic scholar, early

00:34:26.130 --> 00:34:27.510 align:middle line:90%
Christian scholar.

00:34:27.510 --> 00:34:30.830 align:middle line:84%
And Claudia is a seeker
of spiritual wisdom.

00:34:30.830 --> 00:34:33.320 align:middle line:84%
So they talk about the
meaning of this book.

00:34:33.320 --> 00:34:36.090 align:middle line:84%
And what goes on in
this book is this book

00:34:36.090 --> 00:34:41.130 align:middle line:84%
is a story of the surrogacy
of Jesus and Mary Magdalene.

00:34:41.130 --> 00:34:44.070 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they used to
do this thousands of years

00:34:44.070 --> 00:34:47.219 align:middle line:84%
ago, where they would
have a story of someone

00:34:47.219 --> 00:34:48.929 align:middle line:90%
like Joseph in Aseneth.

00:34:48.929 --> 00:34:52.380 align:middle line:84%
But what it actually is
is a contemporary story

00:34:52.380 --> 00:34:54.929 align:middle line:90%
of Jesus and Mary Magdalene.

00:34:54.929 --> 00:34:58.030 align:middle line:10%
So Jacobovici got a hold of--

00:34:58.030 --> 00:35:00.210 align:middle line:10%
he heard about this early text.

00:35:00.210 --> 00:35:03.990 align:middle line:10%
He went to work with a
scholar from Toronto, Barrie

00:35:03.990 --> 00:35:07.170 align:middle line:10%
Wilson, who is a very famous
New Testament scholar.

00:35:07.170 --> 00:35:10.500 align:middle line:84%
And they did modern
translations,

00:35:10.500 --> 00:35:12.930 align:middle line:84%
which means all kinds
of special imaging work

00:35:12.930 --> 00:35:16.080 align:middle line:84%
with ancient manuscripts
of the original manuscript

00:35:16.080 --> 00:35:18.570 align:middle line:90%
in order to get this story out.

00:35:18.570 --> 00:35:20.520 align:middle line:84%
And it's the story
of Jesus falling

00:35:20.520 --> 00:35:24.390 align:middle line:84%
in love with Mary Magdalene and
the story of their marriage.

00:35:24.390 --> 00:35:26.465 align:middle line:90%
And it's beautiful.

00:35:26.465 --> 00:35:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And thus, it has
the redemptive qualities

00:35:28.590 --> 00:35:28.950 align:middle line:90%
but within that.

00:35:28.950 --> 00:35:30.866 align:middle line:84%
>> HAND CLOW: Yeah, well,
it's just beautiful.

00:35:30.866 --> 00:35:32.470 align:middle line:84%
